# apps/web — Web App (React + Vite + TanStack Router)

## Stack

- **React 19** with **Vite**
- **TanStack Router** — file-based routing
- **TanStack Query** — server-state caching
<% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %>- **tRPC client** — typesafe RPC against `apps/api` (Hono backend)
- **Better Auth** — auth client (paired with the Hono API's Better Auth server)
<% } else { %>- **OpenAPI codegen** — wire types are generated from FastAPI's `/openapi.json`
  via `pnpm run codegen` (uses `openapi-typescript`). Re-run after every API
  schema change.
- **Typed fetch client** — see `src/lib/apiClient.ts`. Pure `fetch` wrapper
  around `VITE_API_URL`; no auth, no tRPC. Add the URL to `.env`:
  `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000`.
<% } %><% if (styling === 'tailwind') { %>- **Tailwind CSS v4** + shadcn/ui primitives
<% } else { %>- **Panda CSS** + Ark UI
<% } %>

## Layout

```
apps/web/
├── index.html
├── src/
│   ├── main.tsx           # entry: createRouter + QueryClient<% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %> + tRPC<% } %>
│   ├── routes/            # TanStack file-based routes
│   ├── components/        # shared UI
│   ├── hooks/             # custom React hooks
│   ├── features/          # feature-specific code (created by `feature` generator)
│   └── lib/               # utilities<% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %>
│       ├── trpc.ts        # tRPC client
│       └── auth.ts        # Better Auth client<% } else { %>
│       ├── apiClient.ts   # typed fetch wrapper
│       └── api-schema.ts  # GENERATED from /openapi.json (do not edit)<% } %>
├── vite.config.ts
└── package.json
```

## Run / Test / Build

```sh
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/web dev       # vite dev server
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/web build     # tsc -b && vite build
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/web test      # vitest run
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/web preview   # serve built output
<% if (apiFramework === 'python') { %>pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/web codegen   # refresh api-schema.ts from the running API
<% } %>```

## Conventions

- **Routes are file-based** under `src/routes/`. Use TanStack Router's file conventions (`__root.tsx`, `index.tsx`, `$param.tsx`).
- **Components**: PascalCase, default export, no `any` props. Co-locate small components with the route that owns them; share larger ones via `src/components/`.
- **Server state** lives in TanStack Query.
<% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %>  - Feed it via the tRPC client (`trpc.x.useQuery()`) — do not call `fetch` directly.
<% } else { %>  - Feed it via the typed `api` client (`api.get<Recipe>('/recipes/1')`) and
    TanStack Query. The `api-schema.ts` file is generated; never hand-edit it.
<% } %><% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %>- **Auth state** lives in the Better Auth client hook. Do not roll your own auth context.
<% } %>
- **No barrel files** inside `src/` — import directly from the file that owns the export.

## Adding a new feature

<% if (apiFramework === 'hono') { %>```sh
pnpm nx generate @<%= projectName %>/project-plugin:feature --name <name> --apps web
```
<% } else { %>The `feature` generator currently emits tRPC code (Hono-only). For python
backends, create features manually under `src/features/<name>/`. Co-locate
the React component, the TanStack Query hook, and any feature-specific types
in that directory.
<% } %>
